    <h1>A cry for spring</h1>
  
    <!-- Erstes Bild mit Unterschrift -->
    <img src="../images/story/fuchs.jpg" alt="What a scene!">
    <div class="caption">Fox in the snow - the dream come true for every wildlife photographer</div>

    <!-- Erster Textabschnitt -->
    <p>
    It's so cold, it is nearly impossible to stand still. My fingers are freezing, even though they are packed in my padded, blue gloves and my feet are cold as well, even two pair of socks are
    not helping against the biting frost. At least it stopped snowing. And while everyone is complaining about the white blanket covering the wold and the ice on the streets making it dangerous
    to drive, I cannot help but admiring the beauty of the silent winter.
    <br>
    Originally I wanted to sit in front of the burrow I knew and wait for the fox to appear, but as soon as my destination comes in sight, I realize, that today I might not need the chair I brought 
    with me at all. The snow of the last weeks was enough to cover the whole grasslands by the small river, only the reed is sticking out and shows the courses of the streams. After melting in the winter
    sun and freezing during night I try not to fall while constantly slipping on the dense ice, that cracks below the snow. Although I'm looking for foxes, I normally see some deer around this place. They are
    scratching the frozen earth with their hooves to get at least some green grass.
    </p>

